    • Method Detail

      • requiresApproval

        ApprovalResult requiresApproval()
        Returns:
        an approval result A TransactionSet requires approval if no limits apply or if any of the limits that do apply are exceeded.

      • getTransactionSet

        TransactionSet getTransactionSet()

      • getTransactionsInvolved

        Transaction[] getTransactionsInvolved()
        Returns:
        The transactions in the TransactionSet. For a CheckSet, this includes ONLY the payments that belong to the primary check of the CheckSet. This does NOT include transactions belonging to recurring checks.

      • limitTypeApplies

        boolean limitTypeApplies(AuthorityLimitType type)
        Parameters:
        type - An authority limit type
        Returns:
        true if the limit type applies (e.g., if this is a limit tester for a ReserveSet, and the limit type is "claim total reserves")
